node.text:
Limestone Branch Distillery is releasing 2021 Yellowstone Limited Edition Kentucky Straight Bourbon Whiskey. 

“Featuring the most mature and flavorful 7-year-old and 15-year-old bourbons hand-selected by Limestone Branch Master Distiller Stephen Beam – including select 7-year-old barrels finished in Amarone casks – the latest expression of Yellowstone Limited Edition will be available at retail starting in July at a suggested retail price of $99.99 per bottle.”

- @limestonebranch 

———————————————————————————

node.text:
The 2021 Old Forester Birthday Bourbon has been announced. Details:

“This morning, the brand has finally announced the 2021 release of Birthday Bourbon – the brand’s annual release celebrating the birthday of Old Forester founder George Garvin Brown on September 2nd. 
 
The 21st edition of the brand’s beloved Birthday Bourbon is from 12-year-old barrels and presented at 104 proof.  The batch is comprised of 119 barrels filled on April 16, 2009 and matured in Warehouse G. 
 
This year’s bottle is a bold and compelling offering which showcases a more fruit-forward side of Old Forester with playful berry undertones and summery dessert notes.  Old Forester Birthday Bourbon will be available starting September 2nd at the retail shop at Old Forester Distilling Co. and nationwide for $129.99 in limited 750ml bottles.”

- 📸 @oldforester 

———————————————————————————

#bourbon #bourbonwhiskey #bourbonenthusiast #whiskey #whisky #cheers #drinks #slainte #imbibe #thirstythursday #oldforester #oldforesterbirthdaybourbon #🥃

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The Bourbon Enthusiast on July 07, 2021 tagging @samhoustonbourbon. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text:
All the oak you’d expect from a well-aged Kentucky bourbon. With delightful notes of cherry, vanilla spice, and mild cinnamon. 

Grateful to have been involved with curating this extremely small batch. Sam Houston’s Release No. 6 is a 15 year Kentucky bourbon, non-chill filtered, 103 proof, and carries an SRP of $129 🥃

———————————————————————————

node.text:
Love me some Russell’s Reserve! Recently had the opportunity to select two more tasty barrels: one stellar rickhouse K barrel and a sweet & creamy barrel from the 4th floor of rickhouse F (Tyrone). Can’t wait for these to be bottled! 💯
